10 Interactive UI
*****************

10.1 The ‘*Pending*’ buffer
===========================

‘M-x pending-list’ opens a tabulated-list view with one row per
registered placeholder.

Column      Width     Meaning
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
ID          16        Generated symbol name (‘pending-N’).
Buffer      24        Buffer hosting the placeholder.
Label       30        The label string, truncated.
Status      12        Status keyword, e.g.  ‘:streaming’.
Elapsed     8         Wall-clock seconds since creation.
ETA         8         The placeholder's ETA, or ‘-’.
Group       10        The placeholder's group symbol, or ‘-’.

   Bindings:

‘g’
     Re-read the registry.
‘RET’
     Pop to the placeholder's buffer.
‘c’
     Cancel; reason ‘:cancelled-from-list’.
‘?’
     Open the ‘*Pending: ID*’ description buffer for the row.
‘q’
     Bury the buffer.

   The list auto-refreshes when the registry mutates (controlled by
‘pending-list-auto-refresh’); pressing ‘g’ is still available for
explicit refresh.

10.2 Describing a single placeholder
====================================

 -- Command: pending-describe token
     Pop up a ‘*Pending: ID*’ buffer in ‘pending-description-mode’
     showing structured details about TOKEN: token id, label, status,
     reason, owner buffer, group, indicator type and per-mode state (eta
     / percent / deadline / spinner-style), schedule and resolve
     timestamps, elapsed wall-clock seconds, callback wiring (yes/no for
     on-cancel and on-resolve), and any attached process.  Modeled on
     ‘org-pending’'s ‘org-pending-describe-reglock’.  Interactively,
     prompts with ‘completing-read’ over the registered placeholders.

   Bindings inside the description buffer:

‘g’
     Re-render from the live token slots.
‘RET’
     Pop to the placeholder's buffer (delegates to ‘pending-goto’).
‘c’
     Cancel; reason ‘:cancelled-from-describe’.
‘q’
     Bury the buffer.

10.3 Cancel from point
======================

‘M-x pending-cancel-at-point’ cancels the placeholder under point.  The
library installs an overlay keymap on every placeholder binding ‘RET’
and ‘mouse-1’ to the same command:

 -- Variable: pending-region-map
     Keymap installed on placeholder overlays.  Bound to ‘RET’ and
     ‘mouse-1’ for ‘pending-cancel-at-point’.

10.4 The demo
=============

 -- Command: pending-demo
     Open ‘*pending-demo*’ with three concurrent placeholders
     demonstrating the spinner, ETA, and percent indicators.  They
     resolve themselves over about 12 seconds.  Useful for visual
     inspection of the library on the current theme.


